You can&#39;t do this with `array_map()`, because it doesn&#39;t return an associative array. You have to use nested loops.

```
$priceListFormat = [];
foreach ($priceList as $k1 =&gt; $v1) {
    $r1 = [];
    foreach ($v1 as $k2 =&gt; $v2) {
        $r1[$k2] = number_format($v2, 2, &#39;,&#39;, &#39; &#39;);
    }
    $priceListFormat[$k1] = $r1;
}
```

If your array just contains prices, then you can use `array_walk_recursive()` which will just process all of the leaf nodes of the array.  Then just format each value and replace the existing value with it...

    array_walk_recursive($priceList, function(&amp;$price) 
                    {$price = number_format($price, 2, &#39;,&#39;, &#39; &#39;);});

